35
00:02:46,299 --> 00:02:50,107
<i>[Episode 2]</i>

36
00:02:54,500 --> 00:02:56,899
<i>[Ayako Takigawa]</i>

37
00:02:56,899 --> 00:02:59,415
We only need one teacher.

38
00:02:59,415 --> 00:03:02,683
Don't worry. Mr. Shitou will be the one teaching.

39
00:03:02,683 --> 00:03:06,250
I'm Aoi Shitou. Pleased to meet you.

40
00:03:06,250 --> 00:03:08,600
Then who are you?

41
00:03:08,600 --> 00:03:12,767
I'm... his agent.

42
00:03:12,767 --> 00:03:14,767
I represent him.

43
00:03:14,767 --> 00:03:15,951
An agent?

44
00:03:15,951 --> 00:03:17,760
Yes, ma'am.

45
00:03:19,650 --> 00:03:23,217
This is his PCR test result. Negative.

46
00:03:23,217 --> 00:03:26,426
And this is his resume.

47
00:03:30,475 --> 00:03:35,175
- A humanities degree from Murnau University in Romania?
- Yes.

48
00:03:35,175 --> 00:03:39,031
He used to live abroad so he's good at English. Right?

49
00:03:40,240 --> 00:03:44,825
How about ancient Japanese?

50
00:03:46,784 --> 00:03:50,109
We've got you covered.

51
00:03:50,109 --> 00:03:54,225
<i>She goes, "I prefer my daughter to excel in ancient Japanese,</i>

52
00:03:54,225 --> 00:03:57,517
<i>so we only want someone who can teach that."</i>

53
00:03:57,517 --> 00:04:00,225
<i>She pulled out a Cinderella picture book</i>

54
00:04:00,225 --> 00:04:04,125
<i>and asked me to translate what she reads into old Japanese.</i>

55
00:04:04,125 --> 00:04:06,467
<i>Unbelievable, right?</i>

56
00:04:09,975 --> 00:04:11,159
<i>[Snow White]</i>

57
00:04:11,159 --> 00:04:14,540
"Once upon a time, there lived a beautiful queen

58
00:04:14,540 --> 00:04:18,242
who had a very ugly heart."

59
00:04:18,242 --> 00:04:22,334
Can you say this sentence in ancient Japanese?

60
00:04:23,476 --> 00:04:25,268
That's not Cinderella!

61
00:04:25,268 --> 00:04:27,610
- What?
- Huh?

62
00:04:29,100 --> 00:04:31,976
No, it's nothing at all.

63
00:04:34,357 --> 00:04:38,743
Go on. Translate it.

64
00:04:43,825 --> 00:04:49,850
"A long time ago, there hath lived a quaint queen

65
00:04:49,850 --> 00:04:52,150
who hadst a venomous heart."

66
00:04:57,993 --> 00:04:59,685
You're hired.

67
00:04:59,685 --> 00:05:01,393
Yes!

68
00:05:02,476 --> 00:05:06,818
I'll introduce you to my daughter. Please follow me.

69
00:05:12,600 --> 00:05:18,335
I'd rather have Mr. Shitou go alone. Would you mind leaving?

70
00:05:19,643 --> 00:05:21,718
This way.

71
00:05:27,950 --> 00:05:31,510
Aoi, make me proud!

72
00:05:32,268 --> 00:05:34,468
But why do I feel like I lost?

73
00:05:39,568 --> 00:05:43,809
I'm Hana Takigawa. Nice to meet you.

74
00:05:44,685 --> 00:05:47,126
I'm Aoi Shitou.

75
00:05:47,126 --> 00:05:48,993
I'll leave you two be.

76
00:05:48,993 --> 00:05:50,493
Okay.

77
00:05:57,810 --> 00:05:59,810
Why don't you sit?

78
00:05:59,810 --> 00:06:01,510
Thanks.

79
00:06:03,076 --> 00:06:04,976
Are you good at ancient Japanese?

80
00:06:04,976 --> 00:06:06,935
No, I'm not.

81
00:06:06,935 --> 00:06:10,785
But aren't you here because you passed Mom's test?

82
00:06:10,785 --> 00:06:12,143
Pretty much.

83
00:06:12,143 --> 00:06:14,035
Right.

84
00:06:20,180 --> 00:06:25,718
<i>[A Doll's House by Henrik Ibsen]</i>

85
00:06:27,160 --> 00:06:28,643
You like plays?

86
00:06:28,643 --> 00:06:30,368
What?

87
00:06:30,368 --> 00:06:32,901
Isn't "A Doll's House" a play?

88
00:06:32,901 --> 00:06:37,676
And Henrik Ibsen is Norwegian, right?

89
00:06:38,780 --> 00:06:40,701
You know this book?

90
00:06:40,701 --> 00:06:42,851
Yeah.

91
00:06:43,820 --> 00:06:48,801
You're a tad... too close.

92
00:06:48,801 --> 00:06:50,411
I'm sorry.

93
00:06:50,411 --> 00:06:52,394
Let's crack the door.

94
00:07:00,340 --> 00:07:02,560
Don't worry about her.

95
00:07:08,740 --> 00:07:12,151
Ah, I'm starving.

96
00:07:13,030 --> 00:07:16,918
I need to find a job, too.

97
00:07:20,500 --> 00:07:25,051
<i>[Delivery Staff Wanted]</i>

98
00:07:25,051 --> 00:07:28,901
"Unmer Eats"?

99
00:07:30,576 --> 00:07:33,176
Bingo!

100
00:07:36,210 --> 00:07:38,201
How about, "egregious"?

101
00:07:38,201 --> 00:07:39,351
"Remarkable."

102
00:07:39,351 --> 00:07:41,951
- "Perpend?"
- "To ponder."

103
00:07:41,951 --> 00:07:44,426
- "Besort?"
- "Suitable company."

104
00:07:44,426 --> 00:07:45,601
"I seeth?"

105
00:07:45,601 --> 00:07:47,593
I seeth...?

106
00:07:47,593 --> 00:07:51,076
"Seeth" means...

107
00:07:51,076 --> 00:07:53,010
"Must," right?

108
00:07:53,010 --> 00:07:56,201
No. It means, "I see."

109
00:07:56,201 --> 00:07:58,676
"I see?"

110
00:07:58,676 --> 00:08:01,176
I see!

111
00:08:07,840 --> 00:08:10,576
My clothes are weird, aren't they?

112
00:08:10,576 --> 00:08:13,301
My mom picked out this sweater.

113
00:08:13,301 --> 00:08:16,151
No, they're fine.

114
00:08:17,880 --> 00:08:19,243
Can I ask you something?

115
00:08:19,243 --> 00:08:20,718
What?

116
00:08:20,718 --> 00:08:24,076
Are your curtains always closed?

117
00:08:28,710 --> 00:08:31,327
I prefer it this way.

118
00:08:31,327 --> 00:08:33,301
Me too!

119
00:08:33,301 --> 00:08:36,076
We'll get along, huh.

120
00:09:08,300 --> 00:09:11,526
<i>[Unmer Eats]</i>

121
00:09:16,210 --> 00:09:19,760
We used to deduct the fee from the weekly wages,

122
00:09:19,760 --> 00:09:23,947
but a bunch of boneheads bagged the bags and booked it.

123
00:09:23,947 --> 00:09:28,505
Bagged the bags... Like what I did there?

124
00:09:29,810 --> 00:09:31,485
Not really.

125
00:09:31,485 --> 00:09:33,151
Here's my 4,000 yen.

126
00:09:33,151 --> 00:09:35,033
Appreciate it.

127
00:09:35,033 --> 00:09:38,495
You're a full-fledged delivery guy now. Good luck!

128
00:09:38,495 --> 00:09:40,678
Roger that.

129
00:09:53,520 --> 00:09:55,745
I don't get this part...

130
00:09:55,745 --> 00:09:58,129
Are you hurt?

131
00:09:58,129 --> 00:09:59,604
I bit my lip.

132
00:09:59,604 --> 00:10:00,729
Are you okay?

133
00:10:00,729 --> 00:10:03,162
I'm fine.

134
00:10:03,162 --> 00:10:05,604
Time's up. This is today's payment.

135
00:10:05,604 --> 00:10:07,312
- Thank you.
- Teacher.

136
00:10:07,312 --> 00:10:09,129
We'll see you again next week.

137
00:10:09,129 --> 00:10:10,729
Yes.

138
00:10:14,310 --> 00:10:17,179
Thank you, bye.

139
00:10:39,890 --> 00:10:42,312
What's with the bike?

140
00:10:43,620 --> 00:10:47,487
I thought I'd start cycling to build up stamina.

141
00:10:47,487 --> 00:10:51,187
But more importantly, how'd it go?

142
00:10:51,187 --> 00:10:52,604
It went good.

143
00:10:52,604 --> 00:10:55,470
Here. Today's earnings.

144
00:10:55,470 --> 00:10:58,112
Right on!

145
00:11:01,820 --> 00:11:03,704
Only 20,000 yen?

146
00:11:04,780 --> 00:11:06,645
Wasn't it 50,000?

147
00:11:06,645 --> 00:11:09,904
I went to pay our overdue utility bills.

148
00:11:11,430 --> 00:11:15,454
To think we barely even use electricity.

149
00:11:16,240 --> 00:11:20,504
Bah, it is what it is.

150
00:11:24,495 --> 00:11:26,720
What's wrong?

151
00:11:26,720 --> 00:11:29,329
Something about Hana bothers me.

152
00:11:29,329 --> 00:11:31,220
Hana?

153
00:11:31,220 --> 00:11:33,779
The girl.

154
00:11:33,779 --> 00:11:37,654
So, what about her?

155
00:11:40,220 --> 00:11:45,987
She didn't see me out when I was leaving the house.

156
00:11:47,579 --> 00:11:51,061
Of course not. She's a shut-in.

157
00:11:51,061 --> 00:11:53,002
Still...

158
00:11:54,910 --> 00:11:58,020
It was like she wanted to tell me something.

159
00:12:00,054 --> 00:12:02,529
<i>Thank you, bye.</i>

160
00:12:08,420 --> 00:12:10,729
What do we have here?

161
00:12:11,500 --> 00:12:17,203
Let's see... The delivery destination is...

162
00:12:17,203 --> 00:12:20,720
<i>[Garlic Dumplings Galore]</i>

163
00:12:20,720 --> 00:12:22,845
No!

164
00:12:23,720 --> 00:12:27,987
Garlic Dumplings Galore?

165
00:12:29,770 --> 00:12:32,812
I just can't!

166
00:12:49,480 --> 00:12:51,179
What's wrong?

167
00:13:06,280 --> 00:13:09,629
Teacher, let's go outside.

168
00:14:02,950 --> 00:14:06,480
Last May, my dad left us.

169
00:14:06,480 --> 00:14:09,022
He moved in with someone else.

170
00:14:09,022 --> 00:14:11,647
My mom's been weird ever since.

171
00:14:12,910 --> 00:14:17,164
School reopened in September, but she won't let me go.

172
00:14:17,164 --> 00:14:19,555
Why not?

173
00:14:19,555 --> 00:14:22,514
She thinks I'll leave her, too.

174
00:14:24,180 --> 00:14:26,939
I can't even go out for a second.

175
00:14:26,939 --> 00:14:31,869
She'll cry if I ignore her, and I'll have to console her.

176
00:14:31,869 --> 00:14:34,247
So you'll stay inside forever?

177
00:14:34,247 --> 00:14:38,264
No, I want to leave. I want to live on my own.

178
00:14:38,264 --> 00:14:39,581
Then...

179
00:14:39,581 --> 00:14:42,065
But I can't.

180
00:14:42,065 --> 00:14:46,697
If I leave her, she might die by suicide.

181
00:14:48,950 --> 00:14:51,789
I have to stay with her.

182
00:14:51,789 --> 00:14:54,580
I'm the only one she has now.

183
00:15:22,847 --> 00:15:24,482
She's not home yet.

184
00:15:24,482 --> 00:15:28,305
Phew. I'll go now.

185
00:15:28,305 --> 00:15:30,362
Mom?!

186
00:15:34,910 --> 00:15:37,330
You're fired!

187
00:15:37,330 --> 00:15:40,055
No! I asked him!

188
00:15:40,055 --> 00:15:44,064
It was my fault. I'm sorry.

189
00:15:44,064 --> 00:15:46,489
No, wait!

190
00:15:46,489 --> 00:15:47,880
Mom!

191
00:15:47,880 --> 00:15:52,030
Sweetie, is he more important to you than me?

192
00:15:52,030 --> 00:15:53,881
What?

193
00:15:53,881 --> 00:15:57,231
So you're going to leave me, too!

194
00:15:57,231 --> 00:15:59,356
Just like your father!

195
00:15:59,356 --> 00:16:01,648
Mom...?

196
00:16:02,890 --> 00:16:06,648
You're the only one I have left!

197
00:16:06,648 --> 00:16:10,290
Why can't you understand?!

198
00:16:13,890 --> 00:16:18,115
I'm sorry. I won't go anywhere.

199
00:16:18,115 --> 00:16:21,473
I'll stay by your side forever.

200
00:16:35,060 --> 00:16:39,090
<i>[Toxic Parents.com: How they act]</i>

201
00:16:42,606 --> 00:16:45,065
<i>[Asks "Who's more important?"]</i>

202
00:16:47,165 --> 00:16:52,840
Who gets fired just for taking a walk with their student?

203
00:16:56,450 --> 00:16:58,823
Did you...?

204
00:16:59,700 --> 00:17:03,456
You got fired trying to bite Hana's neck, didn't you?

205
00:17:03,456 --> 00:17:07,081
No! We were just taking a walk.

206
00:17:10,060 --> 00:17:15,849
We could've gotten both blood and money...

207
00:17:17,730 --> 00:17:19,632
Sou.

208
00:17:19,632 --> 00:17:22,007
Will you do me a favor?

209
00:17:42,420 --> 00:17:45,632
Why? How did you get in?

210
00:17:45,632 --> 00:17:48,132
Don't you want to leave?

211
00:17:48,132 --> 00:17:53,874
But... if I leave, Mom will...

212
00:17:53,874 --> 00:17:57,316
"I'm an individual before I'm a mother, a wife."

213
00:17:57,316 --> 00:18:01,791
The protagonist in A Doll's House left thinking that, too.

214
00:18:01,791 --> 00:18:05,557
So... be brave.

215
00:18:07,880 --> 00:18:09,906
Teacher...

216
00:18:18,330 --> 00:18:22,449
Vampires helping humans?

217
00:18:22,449 --> 00:18:25,916
I guess this is another "new normal."

218
00:18:28,490 --> 00:18:30,582
Shoot!

219
00:18:33,291 --> 00:18:35,791
Wait! I think she heard us.

220
00:18:35,791 --> 00:18:37,300
What?

221
00:18:38,157 --> 00:18:41,832
Take Hana outside. I'll distract her by mimicking a cat.

222
00:18:41,832 --> 00:18:43,566
Got it.

223
00:18:51,620 --> 00:18:53,741
Is someone there?

224
00:18:55,640 --> 00:18:57,807
Is that a cat?

225
00:18:59,790 --> 00:19:02,041
Okay, let's go.

226
00:19:11,290 --> 00:19:13,449
I can't.

227
00:19:14,540 --> 00:19:17,874
I have to tell her how I feel first.

228
00:19:17,874 --> 00:19:19,849
Hana...

229
00:19:26,980 --> 00:19:29,483
What are you doing here?

230
00:19:30,941 --> 00:19:33,200
Stop it!

231
00:19:35,950 --> 00:19:37,183
Mom.

232
00:19:37,183 --> 00:19:42,108
Hana, what are you doing? And you, too!

233
00:19:43,080 --> 00:19:47,550
Don't tell me... Were you two trying to take her outside?!

234
00:19:47,550 --> 00:19:50,033
I'm calling the police!

235
00:19:50,033 --> 00:19:51,733
They did nothing wrong!

236
00:19:51,733 --> 00:19:55,741
They were just trying to help me leave!

237
00:19:56,900 --> 00:19:59,208
Leave?

238
00:19:59,208 --> 00:20:02,016
You're going to dump me, too!

239
00:20:02,016 --> 00:20:04,858
Don't say it like that!

240
00:20:06,330 --> 00:20:11,416
Why do you all do this to me?

241
00:20:11,416 --> 00:20:15,441
Do you know how much I've cared for you?

242
00:20:15,441 --> 00:20:19,516
I've loved you so much, all this time.

243
00:20:19,516 --> 00:20:25,950
I can't believe you'd betray me knowing what I've done for you!

244
00:20:29,450 --> 00:20:31,408
Mom...

245
00:20:32,800 --> 00:20:34,575
Hey, lady.

246
00:20:34,575 --> 00:20:39,471
It is the duty of the parents to shower their children with love.

247
00:20:41,840 --> 00:20:45,385
You're not the only one in pain over your husband.

248
00:20:45,385 --> 00:20:49,710
Even your daughter lost her father, too!

249
00:20:49,710 --> 00:20:54,416
But here you are crying that you're the only one suffering.

250
00:20:54,416 --> 00:20:58,100
I'm... We're all suffering, too!

251
00:20:58,100 --> 00:20:59,583
What?

252
00:21:02,260 --> 00:21:05,833
Not just us. It's been hard for everyone!

253
00:21:05,833 --> 00:21:09,625
But we're all doing our best!

254
00:21:15,040 --> 00:21:19,026
So why don't you accept your new life,

255
00:21:19,026 --> 00:21:22,126
your "new normal," and start fresh?

256
00:21:48,500 --> 00:21:49,651
Another order.

257
00:21:49,651 --> 00:21:51,192
Huh? An order?

258
00:21:51,192 --> 00:21:54,292
My bad, gotta run. I'll leave the rest to you.

259
00:21:54,292 --> 00:21:56,392
Seriously?

260
00:22:18,026 --> 00:22:20,834
<i>[To Mr. Sou Kurosawa and Mr. Aoi Shitou]</i>

261
00:22:20,834 --> 00:22:23,890
<i>Thank you for the other day.</i>

262
